            <title>[HIVE-26396] The trunc function has a problem with precision interception and the result has many 0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-26396</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The trunc function has a problem with precision interception and the result has many 0&#65292;There is a problem with the return when the data is of decimal type, and it is displayed normally when the data is of double type&#12290;The test is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1&#65306;Execute on beeline&#65306;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;SELECT &#160;trunc(15.8963,3);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;ins&gt;------------------------&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;_c0 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;ins&gt;------------------------&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt; 15.896000000000000000 &#160;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;ins&gt;------------------------&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
1 row selected (0.074 seconds)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;need return &#8220;15.896&#8221;is correct&#12290;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
